# javascript and classes
--->these are primarily syntactic sugar over existing prototype-based inheritance mechanisms


## OOP
-->it is programming paradigm--> means code structure

## Object means ---> collection of properties and methods
for example ---> toLowerCase, toUpperCase etc.

## why use OOP --->
resolve spaghetti problem and we can also use many features like services


## parts of OOP (components)
--> Object literal {}

# some keywords
--> constructor function
--> Prototypes
--> Classes
--> Instances (new, this)


